## Tools Used

- PEStudio – static analysis of PE files (hashes, metadata, imports).
- FLOSS – string extraction and de-obfuscation.
- Process Explorer – parent-child process relationships, TCP/IP connectivity.
- Process Monitor (Procmon) – detailed process activity logs, filtering for suspicious binaries.
- HxD, Wireshark, CFF Explorer – supporting tools for file and network analysis.

## Findings

- FlareVM provides a complete toolkit for malware analysis.
- Tasks 1–4 demonstrate workflows: static analysis, string extraction, process monitoring, 
- and network traffic inspection.
- Analysts can detect obfuscation, cryptographic use, impersonation, and C2 communication.
- Using multiple tools ensures cross-validation of findings.

## Mitigation / Best Practices

 -Verify file hashes against threat intelligence databases (e.g., VirusTotal).
- Treat executables with suspicious metadata or obfuscation as potential malware.
- Monitor outbound connections for unknown IPs.
- Use multiple tools (PEStudio, FLOSS, Procmon, Procexp) to validate results.
- Conduct analysis only in isolated environments (FlareVM).

